Subject:Re: [CT Birds] geese and ducks do migrate at night
I've known "local" geese to fly at night when disturbed.  Are you sure they were high up?  Being faint enough to be far away doesn't necessarily mean their direction was up, and rain and even clouds absorb sound.

Roy Harvey
Beacon Falls, CT

